      </table><p id="p_8B9A54CACF004B0E93BEA75FBCCCDEE3">For versions of Linux not listed in the table, you can verify
    that you meet the native client dependencies at the library level by using
    the <cmdname id="cmdname_AB3950A2E3A54AB69B79601BCF91AD25">ldd</cmdname> tool and entering this command:</p><codeblock id="codeblock_35B0B1CC778D47B08433B9510C690D8E">prompt&gt; ldd $GFCPP/lib/libgfcppcache.so</codeblock><p id="p_A41F267D58C3463BBB854EDEA9B63EE2">The
    following libraries are external dependencies of the native library,
    <codeph>libgfcppcache.so</codeph>. Verify that the <cmdname>ldd</cmdname>
    tool output includes all of these:</p><sl>
        <sli><codeph>libdl.so.2</codeph> </sli>

        <sli><codeph>libm.so.6</codeph> </sli>

        <sli><codeph>libpthread.so.0</codeph> </sli>

        <sli><codeph>libc.so.6</codeph> </sli>

        <sli><codeph>libz.so.1</codeph></sli>
      </sl><p id="p_A3B0715E0D3B4B808035BAA2CDB5ABDC">For details on the <cmdname id="cmdname_ECAA0438B6A448F5ADEBF96E27A68FD9">ldd</cmdname> tool, see its Linux
    online man page.</p></section>

    <section id="section_E3719D97B6B14E358AFCB5D97C4B581A"><title id="title_EA83681CB321480188148F5A1E9DCF90">Solaris</title><p id="p_5F6E06A33F7340028FB368898013F989">The native client is supported on the
    following Solaris versions:</p><ul id="ul_34ED22AEF4604288B4C2D103E286BCE9">
        <li id="li_0EB9C5F0D31B45EA85B969F14DFC0231">Solaris 9 kernel update 118558-38</li>

        <li id="li_11B117A56FF742689D8985EA5162DE54">Solaris 10 kernel update 118833-24</li>
      </ul></section>
